metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #40
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‘Organic Matr’ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


—— 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter’s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.

metadata.name: Self, Superego #196
metadata.description:
The second installment of the Self trilogy.

Superego is defined as: the one of the three divisions of the psyche in psychoanalytic theory that is only partly conscious, represents internalization of parental conscience and the rules of society, and functions to reward and punish through a system of moral attitudes, conscience, and a sense of guilt.

Please see attached fx(text) article or go to https://ty-vek.art/self-trilogy for more on concept/mechanics/etc. It’s a bit of long read, but worth it.

—————————

All projects are written in vanilla Javascript, composed as SVG and then rendered to a 2d canvas.

There might be slight differences in rendering from browser to browser. This is expected as they might translate the SVG slightly differently. Let's call Chromium renderings canonical. They also render faster there and we love that.

Press "S" to save a PNG.
Press "V" to save a SVG. (Chromium browsers render these pretty well.)

By default, these will render at 2400 x 3200 pixels. This is at density 1.

To render at a larger resolution you can append “&d=2” to the end of the url. This will double the resolution. You can also use 3 or 4 or whatever your browser can handle. Safari tends to have problems with this, so stick with Chromium based browsers (Chrome, Edge, Brave, etc.)

If you want to render as a square image, so it is optimized for ummm.. your pfp or something, you can append “&sq=t” to the url.

If you want to get rid of grain, just append “&g=n”

—————————

https://ty-vek.art/self-trilogy
https://twitter.com/ty__vek
https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/Ty%20Vek/articles

metadata.name: Bacteria Scanner #26
metadata.description: A new bacteria scanning device has arrived.‘Scanner technologies rely upon specific types of chemical compounds called receptors that bind to biological material including microbes, viruses and nucleic acids found within cells. With the arrival of antibiotic resistance strains, scientists must start thinking of alternatives to combat infectious diseases.One solution could lie in identifying and treating bacterial infections earlier before drug resistant organisms develop, for instance using technology to detect new species of microorganisms. New technologies always bring some problems along with benefits.Although bacterial diseases continue to pose significant threats to humans, research shows that we are beginning to see improvements in ways to combat them.As soon as a disease becomes resistant to antibiotics, the situation worsens again.The recent invention of DNA scanners solves this issue and allows scientists to identify and find out about specific bacterium infections before symptoms arise, thus providing a solution with Hydra.

metadata.name: Leeward #5
metadata.description:
At a certain point in time it might look like you live on the leeward side of life. Just keep in mind that there is always a windward side on the other end of that mountain you need to climb.

A lesson of perspective.

This feeling was the main inspiration and driving factor of this piece. And I hope it can convey an amount of those emotions to you through this art piece. :)


- - - - - - - - - - - - - -


I - info about your mint (features, descriptions)
E - export menu where you can export for all sorts of use cases in any resolution you'd like.
Space - save a simple screenshot image of the canvas


- - - - - - - - - - - - - -


Made with love by Wouter Missler with p5.js
